WEBVTT

00:00:04.570 --> 00:00:08.480
<i>Silence Suzuka has made
a miraculous return!</i>

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:30.670 --> 00:00:31.420
{\an8}It's time.

00:00:32.050 --> 00:00:32.760
{\an8}Got it.

00:00:35.470 --> 00:00:36.720
{\an8}Let's go.

00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:39.220
{\an8}Broye Press Conference

00:00:38.150 --> 00:00:41.220
Do you have any comments on
Silence Suzuka's comeback race?

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:42.980
{\an8}It was pretty exciting.

00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:45.600
What is your goal for tomorrow's Japan Cup?

00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:47.980
{\an8}I want to prove that I'm faster
than anyone else out there.

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.100
{\an8}I'm going to make that race
more exciting than Suzuka's.

00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:53.890
It seems Special Week is
doing pretty well lately.

00:00:53.890 --> 00:00:55.110
Are you worried?

00:00:55.110 --> 00:00:57.990
{\an8}Not at all. I will win.

00:00:58.240 --> 00:00:59.620
{\an8}That's all there is to it.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:11.940
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:01:11.940 --> 00:01:18.470
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:20.510 --> 00:01:26.810
{\an8}Umamusume

00:01:22.390 --> 00:01:26.690
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:34.420
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:01:34.420 --> 00:01:39.440
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:45.050
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:51.910
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:57.910
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:01:57.910 --> 00:02:05.190
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:05.190 --> 00:02:10.610
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:02:10.610 --> 00:02:16.080
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:21.590
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:02:21.590 --> 00:02:29.350
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
{\an8}Race 12

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
{\an8}Stage of Dreams

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:42.230
Let's see… Where's the racetrack?

00:02:42.230 --> 00:02:43.760
You there.

00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:46.870
The Tokyo Racecourse
is the next station over.

00:02:46.870 --> 00:02:48.020
What?

00:02:48.190 --> 00:02:50.730
You can take this street straight there.

00:02:50.730 --> 00:02:51.990
It's a bit far.

00:02:51.990 --> 00:02:53.240
It's okay.

00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:55.910
My daughter is running today,
so I'll run, too.

00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:57.290
Wait, hold on…

00:02:57.290 --> 00:03:00.450
Plus, I love running!

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:04.580
I've seen this happen before.

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:09.160
{\an8}Europe's Strongest Horse Girl!!
Broye

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:10.460
They're all talking about Broye.

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:10.460
{\an8}The Winner of the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:12.800
Is Spe still sleeping?

00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:14.040
Yeah.

00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:17.300
I can't eat another bite…

00:03:18.210 --> 00:03:20.650
I want Spe-senpai to win.

00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:22.430
I guess we can agree sometimes.

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:31.400
<i>It's the International
Invitational Japan Cup,</i>

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:34.100
<i>where foreign horse girls get
a chance to race, too.</i>

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:38.110
<i>We have an unprecedented
assortment of talent in this race.</i>

00:03:38.110 --> 00:03:42.200
The most prominent of which
is the French champion,

00:03:43.170 --> 00:03:45.070
Broye.

00:03:48.240 --> 00:03:49.490
She's fast.

00:03:49.490 --> 00:03:52.170
Is she really just warming up?

00:04:05.350 --> 00:04:07.350
I bet Broye's winning today.

00:04:07.350 --> 00:04:10.450
No, I want Special Week to win.

00:04:10.450 --> 00:04:12.390
I'm hoping for a miracle.

00:04:12.390 --> 00:04:13.390
A miracle?

00:04:13.390 --> 00:04:17.110
Well, Suzuka won that race yesterday.
That was basically a miracle.

00:04:17.110 --> 00:04:19.180
You won't see that two days in a row.

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:20.230
Hey, you!

00:04:20.230 --> 00:04:23.900
You know, my daughter
is totally going to win!

00:04:23.900 --> 00:04:25.720
I, uh…

00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:28.740
Are you Spe-chan's mom?

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:30.800
S-Silence…

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:31.950
…Suzuka?

00:04:31.950 --> 00:04:34.630
Sorry, we're a bit late.

00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:35.830
Oh, this is…

00:04:35.830 --> 00:04:37.240
Hello there.

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:39.050
My name is Silence Suzuka.

00:04:39.050 --> 00:04:40.650
I-It's the real…

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:41.160
Huh?

00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:43.480
I'm Special Week's mom!

00:04:43.480 --> 00:04:45.220
Thank you for always taking
care of my daughter.

00:04:46.340 --> 00:04:49.850
Trainer-san, thank you
for having me here today.

00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:54.040
Well, this was the most I
could do to help out today.

00:04:55.430 --> 00:05:00.520
She's sent me all kinds of letters
talking about how cool you are, Suzuka-san.

00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:03.400
That's kind of embarrassing.

00:05:04.100 --> 00:05:07.550
But lately, she says
she wants to run with you.

00:05:07.550 --> 00:05:09.490
She wants to get strong.

00:05:09.490 --> 00:05:15.270
When I got hurt, Spe-chan promised
me that I would run again.

00:05:16.150 --> 00:05:19.840
I was running to make
my own dreams come true,

00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:24.740
but right now, my promise with
Spe-chan is part of my dream.

00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:27.340
That's why I was able to
win that race yesterday.

00:05:27.340 --> 00:05:31.140
I guess she's grown.

00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:32.180
Yeah.

00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:37.850
Well…

00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:42.320
Can she win today's race?

00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:44.540
She can.

00:05:44.540 --> 00:05:45.280
Huh?

00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:49.530
Spe-chan doesn't break her promises.

00:05:51.090 --> 00:05:52.410
You're right.

00:05:54.010 --> 00:05:56.910
Now, we're almost at Spe's waiting room.

00:05:56.910 --> 00:05:59.750
I, uh…

00:06:00.390 --> 00:06:01.080
Hmm?

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:04.750
I'm sure she's nervous.

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:04.760
{\an8}Special Week

00:06:04.750 --> 00:06:06.810
You're too worried about this.

00:06:06.810 --> 00:06:07.510
Yeah.

00:06:13.090 --> 00:06:15.320
Can you hear anything?

00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:17.170
No, nothing.

00:06:17.170 --> 00:06:18.730
I wonder if she's sleeping.

00:06:19.780 --> 00:06:21.230
Everyone's here!

00:06:21.710 --> 00:06:23.020
Urara!

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:24.980
What are you guys doing here?

00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:27.400
I brought souvenirs.

00:06:25.530 --> 00:06:27.400
{\an8}Katsuo Flakes
Katsuo-ya Honpo

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:30.000
You're being too loud!

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:32.250
You're too loud yourself!

00:06:32.250 --> 00:06:33.660
Hey!

00:06:34.390 --> 00:06:36.020
Maruzensky-senpai…

00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:40.540
You wouldn't want to be distracted
before your race, either, would you?

00:06:40.990 --> 00:06:43.290
Now leave.

00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:45.170
What's wrong?

00:06:47.210 --> 00:06:51.440
We wanted to tell Spe-chan
we want her to win.

00:06:51.440 --> 00:06:55.100
But we don't want to
put her under more pressure.

00:06:55.100 --> 00:06:56.800
It's fine!

00:06:56.800 --> 00:06:59.700
It's important to cheer someone
on to help them get stronger.

00:07:00.490 --> 00:07:02.060
That's right.

00:07:03.780 --> 00:07:05.240
All right.

00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:08.280
Huh?

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:09.490
Spe-chan!

00:07:09.490 --> 00:07:11.370
We came to cheer you on.

00:07:11.370 --> 00:07:11.910
Yeah.

00:07:12.610 --> 00:07:14.910
Yeah, thanks!

00:07:14.910 --> 00:07:17.670
I'll cheer you on as loud as I can.

00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:18.890
Me, too!

00:07:18.890 --> 00:07:19.970
Right!

00:07:19.970 --> 00:07:25.700
Oh, yeah! How do you say,
"Let's have a good race," in French, El?

00:07:25.700 --> 00:07:27.000
A good race?

00:07:28.290 --> 00:07:31.510
Oh, I happen to know!

00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:35.940
That's how!

00:07:36.890 --> 00:07:38.720
Thank you, El-chan!

00:07:38.720 --> 00:07:40.890
Anyway, I'll be going!

00:07:45.860 --> 00:07:48.030
See you…

00:07:50.900 --> 00:07:53.370
I remember the day when
she first transferred in.

00:07:53.370 --> 00:07:54.660
Yeah.

00:07:54.660 --> 00:07:56.410
I wonder if she'll be okay.

00:07:56.410 --> 00:07:58.000
She beat me.

00:07:58.000 --> 00:07:59.540
She better not lose.

00:08:00.260 --> 00:08:02.660
It's nice to have colleagues.

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:17.540
Broye's so cool.

00:08:17.540 --> 00:08:19.060
She's running against us, you know.

00:08:19.390 --> 00:08:23.310
Yeah, but I honestly think
this'll be fun to watch.

00:08:23.310 --> 00:08:26.740
Part of me really wants to see Broye run.

00:08:27.990 --> 00:08:30.280
I guess we're just in sync today.

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:36.680
I showed Spe-chan's mom to her seat.

00:08:36.680 --> 00:08:39.040
She decided not to see
Spe after all, huh?

00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:40.210
Yeah.

00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:42.540
Suzuka, watch closely.

00:08:43.300 --> 00:08:44.150
Yeah.

00:08:44.810 --> 00:08:48.250
They're cheering so much
for her instead of me.

00:08:48.250 --> 00:08:50.660
I wanted to race against her, too.

00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:51.880
Me, too.

00:08:51.880 --> 00:08:53.970
I want to test her strength.

00:08:53.970 --> 00:08:56.290
Everyone's expecting a lot from her.

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:07.540
Spe-chan!

00:09:07.540 --> 00:09:11.020
I want her to win for
us Japanese horse girls.

00:09:11.020 --> 00:09:14.280
Sometimes, people lose unexpectedly…

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:18.280
<i>"Eclipse first, the rest nowhere."</i>

00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:21.540
<i>You're going to have to push yourself.</i>

00:09:23.290 --> 00:09:26.120
I want to be the top horse girl in Japan!

00:09:28.520 --> 00:09:31.250
<i>If she wins this, she might be
able to call herself that.</i>

00:09:31.850 --> 00:09:34.880
Everyone, watch this closely.

00:09:34.880 --> 00:09:35.720
Right!

00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:38.610
I want Spe-chan to win.

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:45.520
Yeah, but watching this… I really feel
like I want to be up there with them.

00:09:45.520 --> 00:09:48.270
And you will, someday. After me.

00:09:48.270 --> 00:09:49.650
I'll be first!

00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:51.720
What are you fighting about?!

00:09:51.720 --> 00:09:53.360
We're going to send her our energy.

00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:54.860
What?!

00:09:54.860 --> 00:10:00.570
{\an8}Win, win!

00:09:55.330 --> 00:09:57.540
Does that really work?

00:09:57.540 --> 00:09:58.590
Right, Suzuka?

00:09:58.590 --> 00:09:59.710
Win…

00:09:58.840 --> 00:10:00.570
{\an4}Energy

00:09:59.710 --> 00:10:00.570
What?

00:10:50.040 --> 00:10:54.040
Umamusume
Pretty Derby

00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:58.310
Special Week is entering the track!

00:10:59.550 --> 00:11:00.760
Spe-chan!

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:01.720
Spe-senpai!

00:11:01.720 --> 00:11:03.430
Be strong!

00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:04.720
Spe-chan!

00:11:04.720 --> 00:11:06.440
You can do it!

00:11:06.440 --> 00:11:08.050
I'm getting nervous!

00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:09.810
Me, too.

00:11:10.730 --> 00:11:11.650
<i>Spe…</i>

00:11:12.770 --> 00:11:14.330
<i>Don't get hurt out there.</i>

00:11:16.570 --> 00:11:18.200
Spe-chan!

00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:18.970
Everyone!

00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:20.030
Yo!

00:11:20.420 --> 00:11:22.910
Has the plan changed at all?

00:11:22.910 --> 00:11:26.280
Plans are the last thing
you need to worry about now.

00:11:26.280 --> 00:11:28.150
That's true.

00:11:28.900 --> 00:11:30.120
I…

00:11:30.120 --> 00:11:33.040
I've selfishly placed my dreams in you.

00:11:33.040 --> 00:11:37.830
I want you to beat Broye in a race that would
let you call yourself the best in Japan.

00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:40.760
Spe, please make my dream come true.

00:11:42.530 --> 00:11:43.310
Right!

00:11:43.310 --> 00:11:45.080
I'm going to win!

00:11:54.520 --> 00:11:58.270
Broye has stepped onto the turf.

00:11:58.270 --> 00:12:00.020
Those are some deafening shouts.

00:12:02.740 --> 00:12:03.620
Spe…

00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:05.620
Have fun.

00:12:05.620 --> 00:12:06.770
Right.

00:12:06.770 --> 00:12:08.010
I'll be back.

00:12:10.100 --> 00:12:14.810
<i>All of the horse girls running in the
Japan Cup have made their way out.</i>

00:12:15.790 --> 00:12:19.300
<i>Broye's presence out there is staggering.</i>

00:12:19.300 --> 00:12:22.730
Yes, she's practically undefeated.

00:12:22.730 --> 00:12:27.070
She beat El Condor Pasa in the
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:12:27.070 --> 00:12:29.680
What makes Broye so strong?

00:12:30.050 --> 00:12:33.730
Her strength is in her
incredible racing intuition.

00:12:33.730 --> 00:12:37.440
She handles her early, middle,
and late game perfectly.

00:12:37.870 --> 00:12:40.690
<i>We hope Special Week does
great out there, too.</i>

00:12:40.690 --> 00:12:42.210
Broye-san…

00:12:42.210 --> 00:12:43.200
Bonjour.

00:12:43.200 --> 00:12:44.700
{\an8}Hello, dear.

00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:53.040
{\an8}I was just greeting you.

00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:55.080
Well…

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:58.540
<i>I think this is how you say,
"Let's have a good race."</i>

00:12:58.920 --> 00:13:00.800
{\an8}Don't get too cocky!

00:13:15.140 --> 00:13:16.770
Nice to meet you.

00:13:16.770 --> 00:13:18.270
{\an8}Don't get too cocky!

00:13:18.270 --> 00:13:18.830
What?

00:13:18.830 --> 00:13:19.900
Glad to meet you.

00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:21.650
{\an8}Don't get too cocky!

00:13:21.340 --> 00:13:22.290
{\an8}What?

00:13:24.150 --> 00:13:28.710
Doesn't Broye-san look
even more intimidating?

00:13:30.730 --> 00:13:33.770
What did you tell Spe-chan to say?

00:13:33.770 --> 00:13:35.380
That's a secret.

00:13:41.930 --> 00:13:43.920
<i>The promise with my mom…</i>

00:14:11.810 --> 00:14:14.760
<i>I'm going to keep my promise.</i>

00:14:17.570 --> 00:14:20.710
<i>I'm going to be the best horse girl in Japan.</i>

00:14:24.450 --> 00:14:25.710
<i>They've entered the gates.</i>

00:14:26.580 --> 00:14:29.090
<i>The Japan Cup is finally going to start!</i>

00:14:32.850 --> 00:14:33.970
{\an8}We'll crush you!

00:14:34.720 --> 00:14:36.710
<i>The gates have opened!</i>

00:14:40.530 --> 00:14:44.110
<i>Both Special Week and Broye are in the rear!</i>

00:14:44.110 --> 00:14:46.010
Did Broye start late?

00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:48.610
No, she's feeling Spe out.

00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:49.870
You can do it, Spe-chan!

00:14:49.870 --> 00:14:51.220
Go!

00:14:51.220 --> 00:14:53.070
She's after Spe-chan?

00:14:53.490 --> 00:14:57.080
It's the same as when she followed me.

00:14:57.080 --> 00:14:59.930
<i>The horse girls are making the first turn.</i>

00:15:01.580 --> 00:15:03.040
{\an8}…She told us not to get cocky?

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:04.040
{\an8}Guess she just has a big mouth.

00:15:07.300 --> 00:15:09.380
They've passed the 1,000
meter mark in a minute.

00:15:09.380 --> 00:15:10.380
That's an average pace.

00:15:10.820 --> 00:15:12.430
<i>Who's going to make their move?</i>

00:15:12.430 --> 00:15:15.770
<i>Special Week, the representative
for Japan, is following,</i>

00:15:15.770 --> 00:15:17.690
<i>and behind her, Broye.</i>

00:15:20.060 --> 00:15:22.150
{\an8}Sorry, but I know exactly how you operate.

00:15:22.690 --> 00:15:24.310
{\an8}How are you going to make your move?

00:15:34.330 --> 00:15:38.160
<i>Special Week and Broye are
still following up the rear.</i>

00:15:44.960 --> 00:15:46.520
{\an8}She's moved up!

00:15:44.960 --> 00:15:46.170
She made her move.

00:15:46.520 --> 00:15:48.420
<i>Special Week has moved up!</i>

00:15:48.420 --> 00:15:50.170
{\an8}Within expectations.

00:15:50.510 --> 00:15:52.930
<i>Broye has started moving up from behind, too!</i>

00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:58.310
Oh, my god!

00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:03.810
<i>They've passed the great zelkova tree
and are speeding up even further!</i>

00:16:04.190 --> 00:16:06.520
{\an8}She made her move early… Now's my chance!

00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:08.530
You can do it, Spe-senpai!

00:16:08.530 --> 00:16:11.080
Let her have it!

00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:13.810
This is a nice development.

00:16:13.810 --> 00:16:15.520
Is it possible she…

00:16:15.520 --> 00:16:17.370
Yeah. She can do it.

00:16:17.370 --> 00:16:18.720
Go! Go!

00:16:18.720 --> 00:16:20.000
It's just the two of you!

00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:23.020
<i>They've passed the third corner
and are onto the fourth.</i>

00:16:23.020 --> 00:16:25.500
<i>Special Week is gaining
from the outside, but…</i>

00:16:27.560 --> 00:16:29.880
<i>Broye is gaining from even further out!</i>

00:16:32.300 --> 00:16:33.930
{\an8}I'm going to shatter your will!

00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:43.140
{\an8}I'm not gaining…

00:16:43.770 --> 00:16:44.520
{\an8}This girl…!

00:16:53.860 --> 00:16:54.990
{\an8}I'm finishing this!

00:16:55.690 --> 00:16:57.240
<i>They're passing the fourth corner!</i>

00:16:58.410 --> 00:16:59.490
Spe!

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:02.780
They've entered the last stretch!

00:17:02.780 --> 00:17:04.290
Special Week's not falling behind!

00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:06.250
<i>She's still gaining!</i>

00:17:06.710 --> 00:17:08.000
{\an8}I'm not losing this…

00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:09.420
{\an8}I'm going to win!

00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:18.510
<i>Special Week has taken the lead!</i>

00:17:18.510 --> 00:17:20.190
You can do it, Spe-chan!

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:21.260
Just a bit further!

00:17:21.260 --> 00:17:22.390
Go!

00:17:23.140 --> 00:17:24.600
Go.

00:17:24.600 --> 00:17:25.400
Go!

00:17:25.400 --> 00:17:26.810
You can do it, Spe!

00:17:26.810 --> 00:17:28.190
Go!

00:17:31.690 --> 00:17:34.440
<i>Can Broye catch up to Special Week?</i>

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:56.220
Spe-chan!

00:18:12.820 --> 00:18:15.690
<i>Special Week! Special Week!</i>

00:18:16.690 --> 00:18:18.150
It's Special Week!

00:18:18.150 --> 00:18:20.620
<i>It's her!</i>

00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:30.520
<i>Japan's representative,
Special Week, has won!</i>

00:18:34.130 --> 00:18:36.340
Yes!

00:18:36.820 --> 00:18:39.220
Special Week has won!

00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:50.360
Special Week!

00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:56.680
I won?

00:18:56.990 --> 00:18:58.360
{\an8}This was your win.

00:18:59.110 --> 00:19:00.500
Broye-san…

00:19:03.810 --> 00:19:05.410
Thank you.

00:19:06.660 --> 00:19:09.160
{\an8}I give this victory to you.

00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:10.870
{\an8}But I'll be winning again soon.

00:19:10.870 --> 00:19:13.130
I…

00:19:13.130 --> 00:19:15.340
"Don't get too cocky"?

00:19:17.380 --> 00:19:18.840
Right!

00:19:23.220 --> 00:19:24.490
Are you watching?

00:19:24.490 --> 00:19:29.000
That's our horse girl, the best in Japan.

00:19:40.660 --> 00:19:44.120
<i>She came in first,
carrying everyone's dreams with her.</i>

00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:46.330
<i>She's pretty impressive.</i>

00:19:46.330 --> 00:19:49.080
Special Week-san, how do you feel?

00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:50.760
Well, I…

00:19:52.310 --> 00:19:55.750
{\an8}I'm very happy. Thank you.

00:19:54.040 --> 00:19:56.500
Some things about her
just don't change.

00:19:56.500 --> 00:20:00.650
Now that you've won the Japan Cup,
what would you like to do next?

00:20:01.060 --> 00:20:02.510
Next…

00:20:04.710 --> 00:20:06.010
Well…

00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:11.940
I want to be a horse girl who can continue
to make everyone's dreams come true,

00:20:11.940 --> 00:20:16.270
and I want to give the people
who cheered me on dreams, too.

00:20:16.270 --> 00:20:18.780
That's the type of horse girl I want to be!

00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:34.540
<i>Her ability to carry those dreams
must be what gives her power.</i>

00:20:35.490 --> 00:20:37.420
<i>To carry everyone's dreams.</i>

00:22:44.730 --> 00:22:48.360
<i>Now it's my turn to make
your dream come true.</i>

00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:09.490
{\an8}Sometime later…

00:23:06.840 --> 00:23:10.490
